result.execSummary:
The defendant Andrew T Gonring was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: If a Wisconsin State Prison sentence is imposed, outstanding financial obligations shall be paid from prison funds at a rate to be determined by Dept of Corrections and the balance due as a condition of extended supervision.  If extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with financial obligations owing, a judgment shall be entered.

Defendant shall have no contact with M.M.K., her family or her residence.
Defendant shall not possess or use a computer or any technological device with internet capabilities except for work or school purposes and then only with permission of the agent.
Defendant shall not view sexually explicit materials.  
Defendant shall have no contact with minors unless his Probation Agent approves.
Defendant shall not enter establishments where primary purpose is the sale/service of alcohol.

Defendant shall obtain/maintain a stable residence.
Defendant shall undergo sex offender treatment and sex offender registration.
Defendant shall submit to random drug screens including blood, breath or urine.
